TY  - JOUR
AU  - Rachwalski, Mark
AU  - Wen, Quan
T1  - Idiosyncratic Risk Innovations and the Idiosyncratic Risk-Return
                    Relation
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raw002
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
SP  - 303
EP  - 328
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Stocks with increases in idiosyncratic risk tend to earn low subsequent returns
                    for a few months. However, high idiosyncratic risk stocks eventually earn
                    persistently high returns. These results are consistent with positively priced
                    idiosyncratic risk and temporary underreaction to idiosyncratic risk
                    innovations. Because risk levels and innovations are correlated, the relation
                    between historical idiosyncratic risk and returns may reflect both risk premiums
                    and underreaction and yield misleading inference regarding the price of risk.
                    The results reconcile previous work offering conflicting evidence on the price
                    of idiosyncratic risk and help to discriminate among explanations for the
                    idiosyncratic risk-return relation.Received November 24, 2014; accepted December 20, 2015 by Editor Jeffrey
                    Pontiff.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raw002
ER  - 



